{
  "article_id": "BuffaloCourierRecord1897",
  "paragraphs": [
    [
      {
        "text": "A party of young scientists, acting under the auspices of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Harvard University",
        "entity_key": "in_harvard",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Cambridge, Mass.",
        "entity_key": "ci_ca",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and "
      },
      {
        "text": "Leland Stanford, Jr., University",
        "entity_key": "in_stanford",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Palo Alto, Cal.",
        "entity_key": "ci_paloalto",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", are now exploring the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", off the coast of "
      },
      {
        "text": "alifornia",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and they have sent word to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "mainland",
        "entity_key": "re_mld",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "that their archaeological and ethnological discoveries have been so marvelously rich that the expedition will be prolonged several months."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "have long been known among the old-time residents of "
      },
      {
        "text": "California",
        "entity_key": "st_cal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "as the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Golgotha of the Pacific",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", for nowhere else in the world are there probably as many human bones and skeletons lying exposed to the elements as in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". There are several spots on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "where whole acres of rocks and sandy waste are thickly strewn with human bones. Only a year ago several men came home to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "ci_ven",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "with a barrel of Indian crude implements and over 200 whitened skulls, which the men said they had picked from among thousands of skulls. A dozen of these fast-crumbling skulls were sent to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Smithsonian Institution",
        "entity_key": "mu_smithsonian",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Washington",
        "entity_key": "ci_dc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and also to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Harvard Univeristy",
        "entity_key": "in_harvard",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Cambridge",
        "entity_key": "ci_ca",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". The ethnologists at both institutions were immediately interested, and they declared the skulls were those of a race of Indian giants. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Harvard University",
        "entity_key": "in_harvard",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "lost no time in sending an expedition to explore the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "scientifically."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Probably no region in the United States offers greater inducements to students in anthropology and ethnology than "
      },
      {
        "text": "these islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Ten years ago a resident of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Fransisco",
        "entity_key": "ci_sf",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "offered to pay the expenses of an expedition of scientists who should spend a summer in exploring "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente",
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "Islands, and to give the results of their finds to the "
      },
      {
        "text": "State university at Berkely",
        "entity_key": "in_ucb",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", but there arose such jealously among the leaders of the proposed expedition that the offer was withdrawn. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "constitute California's only archipelago, with the possible exception of the ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "rocky and scanty Farallone Islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_far",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They have been objects of romantic legends, curiosity and mystery for two generations or more. Notwithstanding all ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "are within eighty-two miles of the ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "California shore",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", they are solitary and unfrequented, and years roll by with visits to them of fewer than twenty people. Each island has its own particular traditions and each has countless traces of an occupation by thousands of ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Indians",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "When ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Juan Rodriquez Cabrillo",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "jca",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", the Portuguese navigator, sailed up the ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "coast of California",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in 1542 he stopped for a day or two at each of the ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel Islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and his records bear testimony that on the islands of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Catalina",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scatalina",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Clemente",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_scl",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "there was \"",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a vigorous and lusty race of natives",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who thronged the shores of the little bays and headlands,\" and gazed in wonder at ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the white-sailed ship",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "sh_salvador",
          "sh_lavictoria"
        ],
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the navigators",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "jca",
          "bfe"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Today ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "stand as they did more than 350 years ago, but ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the natives",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "natam_NicolenoTongva",
          "natam_GabrilenoTongva",
          "natam_chumash"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "are only a memory, represented by immense quantities of stone implements, barrels of fine wampum and literally cart loads of human bones.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas Island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", which lies eighty miles off the little city of "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Buenaventura",
        "entity_key": "ci_ven",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "(recently called by the more modern and easier name of "
      },
      {
        "text": "Ventura",
        "entity_key": "ci_ven",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "), is the most interesting of all the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from many points of view. As far back as the memory of any person in "
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California",
        "entity_key": "re_socal",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "runs hundreds of white skeletons have dotted the valleys and hillsides. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Strange utensils of serpentine, sandstone and steatite are found there among the human bones, and ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "its inhabitants",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "have a history so curious that it is difficult of comprehension.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "In 1835 ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the Franciscan padres in the Santa Barbara mission",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "aji",
          "ndur",
          "misfats"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", learning that there were but ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "sixteen of the strange Indian race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "then living, determined to rescue them from ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". They went over in ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "and succeeded, at they thought, in getting all on board. At the last moment ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an Indian woman",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "returned for ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her child",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lwchild",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", and one of the frequent storms of the ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "springing up, ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the sloop",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "was driven away. ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "The sloop",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_peoresnada",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "went on the rocks of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Point Conception",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_pc",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "all on board",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "bhagroup",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "were lost.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Sixteen years later ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Capt. George Nidever",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "two men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "tje",
          "nativeamericans"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "went from ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the coast",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "re_calcoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "in ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a sloop",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": "to hunt sea otters off ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". On landing they, like Crusoe, were astonished to discover human footprints in the sand. They saw no one, however, and a storm compelled them to put to sea. ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "It was two years later that ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the captain",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "gni",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", revolving in his mind the sight of the footprints in ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the uncanny island",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", determined to go and discover and bring over ",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the lonely woman",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "of whom he had vaguely heard.",
        "tropes": [
          4,
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Men",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_keys": [
          "cdi",
          "col",
          "cook",
          "msh",
          "poli",
          "nsk",
          "hva"
        ],
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "accompanied him, and at length they saw on the surf-beaten shore ",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "a woman",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "with long tawny hair, dressed in a queer garb of colored birdskins and scraping with a bone knife the blubber from a seal.",
        "tropes": [
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "They surrounded and approached her stealthily. Although suddenly confronted, she did not appear to be in the least afraid, but smiled, and then, falling on her knees, prayed to the sun.",
        "tropes": [
          1,
          4
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "She offered no objection when by signs she was made to understand that she was to go with them in ",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the boat",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ],
        "entity_key": "sh_nidever",
        "entity_type": "ship"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          1
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "They reached "
      },
      {
        "text": "Santa Barbara",
        "entity_key": "ci_sb",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "across the rough sea, and the first thing "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "saw was "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. S. L. Shaw",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", who is still living at the age of 80 years, riding a horse. She had never seen a spectacle like it and thought "
      },
      {
        "text": "the man",
        "entity_key": "ssh",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "and horse were one, and she knelt on the shore and offered her devotion to it. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Two weeks afterward ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the last inhabitant of rock-ribbed, tempest-beaten San Nicolas",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "died from eating food to which she was unaccustomed, and the curtain fell on ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "her race",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "forever.",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In speaking of that death at a meeting of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Southern California Medical Society",
        "entity_key": "socalmedicalsociety",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "the other day "
      },
      {
        "text": "Dr. Walter Lindley",
        "entity_key": "wli",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "said that if "
      },
      {
        "text": "the woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "could have been spared for a few years a story of "
      },
      {
        "text": "one of the strangest races",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "that ever lived in the "
      },
      {
        "text": "southwest",
        "entity_key": "re_sw",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "and had had no contamination from the whites, might have been learned. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The woman",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": ", known as the \"lone woman of San Nicolas,\" has been the subject of a score of romances and poems and food for a lot of philosophy of the "
      },
      {
        "text": "coast",
        "entity_key": "re_paccoast",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Nothing more desolate than the general appearance of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "can be imagined. As far as the eye can trace there are barren levels, with innumerable circular depressions, showing where primitive dwellings once stood. Not a vestige remains of the materials used in the construction of these rancherias. Hundreds of shell mounds are scattered about and are found to consist of astonishing numbers of mollusks, the bones of every species of fish found in the channel, skeletons of seals, sea elephants, whales, sea otter, the island fox and various aquatic birds. Without question these animals were used for food by "
      },
      {
        "text": "the tribes that once thronged the island",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". There are also numerous canine skeletons, several of which indicate a species of bull terrier."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "Judging from the immense quantities of dead land mollusks everywhere there must have been a time when "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "supported luxuriant vegetation. Of all this verdure nothing is seen today but a few stunted thorn bushes, and now and then a cactus forlornly reaching its grotesque arms out of the interminable sweeps of sand. An examination of some of the mounds discloses all sorts of curious utensils, stone cooking pots, water ollas, mortars, pestles, drills, bone needles and fish hooks, shell beads, charm stones, pipes, cups and a few arrow heads, spear points and swords made of bone. "
      },
      {
        "text": "The absence of any weapons proves the peaceful attributes of ",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "the islanders",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Small imitations of boats and fishes carved from crystallized talc and serpentine also show a rudimentary knowledge of the art of sculpture.",
        "tropes": [
          3
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "In many places conical piles of small black pebbles contrast oddly with the white sand. In some instances these pebbles were closely packed in abalone shells. No trace is seen of the brush pens in which the "
      },
      {
        "text": "lone woman of San Nicholas",
        "entity_key": "lw",
        "entity_type": "person"
      },
      {
        "text": "for years found her only shelter from the cutting wind and sand. "
      },
      {
        "text": "Every foot of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "this strange island",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is eloquent of the extinction of ",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "an almost unheard-of people",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ],
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": ".",
        "tropes": [
          6
        ]
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "The shore line is of course [coarse] sandstone, burrowed by the pounding surf into fantastic alcoves, bridges, columns and caves. Sometimes these savage cuts form rude effigies bearing surprising likeness to living creatures. One of the most conspicuous is the exact counterpart of the neck, breast and body of a bird with an alert, hooded head. This piece of nature's sculpture must be forty feet long, and beheld from a distance looks as perfect as if fashioned by man.",
        "tropes": [
          5
        ]
      },
      {
        "text": "Going westward from this gnawed, surf-lashed wall the ground makes a gentle descent to a wide mesa, terminating in a steep escarpment. The atmosphere from this elevation is so deliciously clear that the eye can readily distinguish the peak tops of all the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ", although several of them are forty miles away. Immediately at one's feet there stretches a dreary desert."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "A singular characteristic of the place were the heaps of the bones of whales, their arrangement and packing so systematically correct as to have withstood a century's sweep of winds over the exposed point. Only one human skeleton has ever been found here. All around are casts of roots of trees in the shifting sand, ranging all the way in size from coarse fiber to several inches in diameter. These semipetrefactions, are intact, the wind having swept them clean of the loose earth. They yield a metallic ring when tapped with a rock or shell. A still more remarkable feature of this desert is a sparse stone forest, the broken columns of trunks of trees composed of indurated sand."
      }
    ],
    [
      {
        "text": "At the extreme western end of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "there is a colossal precipice 1,000 feet in height, its chasamed and slitted face softened by a luxuriant growth of emerald moss and lichens. The strangest of all the sights on "
      },
      {
        "text": "this island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "is to be seen on the broad plateau south of the Chinese camp at "
      },
      {
        "text": "Coral harbor",
        "entity_key": "re_coralharbor",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": ". Here acres of the sand are littered with thousands of disjointed skeletons. Measurements have been made by several scientists of the thigh, leg and arm bones, and literally bushels of skulls and other parts of the human frame have been brought to "
      },
      {
        "text": "Los Angeles",
        "entity_key": "ci_la",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "from "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "for investigation. A physician recently counted there over 1,200 skulls in one locality. Some were almost dropping to pieces from long exposure to the sun and water. The general opinion is that the physique of "
      },
      {
        "text": "the Indian race",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "that swarmed over "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "then was much larger than that of any civilized race of today and that some of them must have been seven feet three inches tall. The skulls of "
      },
      {
        "text": "this extinct tribe",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "often measure several inches more than some of the large skulls of today. Many skulls found lying about on "
      },
      {
        "text": "the island",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "show that their possessors must have suffered death from a club or blunt battle ax. No one has yet found a skull on "
      },
      {
        "text": "San Nicolas",
        "entity_key": "i_sn",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "that shows marks of a bullet. There are many collar bones and shoulder blades broken and crushed, so that it is evident that their owners were killed by some instrument like a war club of bowlder. Scientists say the favorite weapon in warfare with the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Aleutian savage tribes",
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "natam_aleuts"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "a century or more ago was a club or bludgeon, and this fact fits with the stray tradition that the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Aleutians",
        "entity_keys": [
          "rfurcompany",
          "natam_aleuts"
        ],
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "came down and completely destroyed "
      },
      {
        "text": "the people",
        "entity_key": "natam_NicolenoTongva",
        "entity_type": "org"
      },
      {
        "text": "on the "
      },
      {
        "text": "Channel islands",
        "entity_key": "i_chi",
        "entity_type": "place"
      },
      {
        "text": "about 1780."
